statement.p:
We should also test when the <md> is within a list.




Start a list.






\begin{aligned}
    2x+1 \amp= 3
    \end{aligned}

Now subtract 1 from each side.

\begin{aligned}
    2x   \amp= 2
    \end{aligned}

Now divide by 2 on each side.

\begin{aligned}
    x    \amp= 1
    \end{aligned}




Still in the list?
